The paper proposes a method for image inpainting using a Deep Convolutional Generative Adversarial Network (DCGAN), which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The loss function used in the proposed method consists of both contextual and perceptual losses, which are commonly used in deep learning models for image processing and generation (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on two datasets, CelebA and SVHN, which are commonly used in computer vision research (cs.GR). Finally, the paper focuses on achieving pixel-level photorealism, which is a key aspect of multimedia processing (cs.MM).
